## 🎨 Frontend (React + Vite)
The frontend is a Single Page Application built with React, Vite (for fast building), and Tailwind CSS (for styling).

### Root Configuration Files
*   **`package.json` & `package-lock.json`**: Lists all the external libraries your project needs (like React, Axios, React Router) and script commands (like `npm run dev`).
*   **`vite.config.js`**: Settings for Vite, the tool that runs your local development server and bundles your code for production.
*   **`tailwind.config.js` & `postcss.config.js`**: Configuration files for Tailwind CSS, allowing you to customize your styling theme, colors, and layout utilities.
*   **`eslint.config.js`**: Rules for finding and fixing problems in your JavaScript code (Code Linting).
*   **`index.html`**: The single HTML file that loads your React application.

### 🚀 Application Entry & Global Settings (`src/`)
*   **`main.jsx`**: The starting point of your React app. It grabs the `App` component and injects it into `index.html`.
*   **`App.jsx`**: The main container component. It sets up "Routing" (React Router), dictating which Page component to show based on the URL the user is visiting.
*   **`App.css` & `index.css`**: Your main stylesheet files. `index.css` is usually where Tailwind is imported.
*   **`constants.js`**: A place to store global variables (like your backend API base URL or role names) so you don't have to re-type them everywhere.
*   **`utils.js`**: A file for reusable helper functions (e.g., formatting dates, capitalizing text).
*   **`api/axios.js`**: Configures Axios (the tool used to make HTTP requests to your backend). It's usually set up here to automatically attach the JWT token to every request.

### 🧩 Components (`src/components/`)
Reusable UI building blocks used across different pages.
*   **`Navbar.jsx`**: The top navigation bar (usually contains the profile icon and logout button).
*   **`Sidebar.jsx`**: The side menu for navigating between different dashboard views.
*   **`Layout.jsx`**: A wrapper component that combines the Navbar, Sidebar, and the main content area so you don't have to rewrite them on every page.
*   **`EventCard.jsx`**: A small, rectangular card that displays a quick summary of an event (title, date).
*   **`EventDetailDrawer.jsx`**: A sliding side-panel that pops out to show the full details of an event when clicked.
*   **`RegistrationModal.jsx`**: A pop-up window asking the user to confirm they want to register for an event.
*   **`ApprovalModal.jsx`**: A pop-up window used by faculty to approve or reject an event proposal, often including a space for comments.
*   **`ActivityPanel.jsx`**: A section that shows a timeline or list of recent notifications/activities.
*   **`PageHeader.jsx`**: The title bar at the top of a page view.
*   **`StatCard.jsx`**: A small widget displaying numbers, like "Total Events" or "Pending Approvals", used on dashboards.
*   **`WorkFlowBadge.jsx`**: A visual pill/tag showing the status of an event (e.g., green for Approved, yellow for Pending).

### 🖼️ Layouts (`src/layouts/`)
*   **`DashboardLayout.jsx`**: A specific layout structure used for logged-in users, enforcing the Sidebar and Navbar structure around the main page content.

### 📄 Pages (`src/pages/`)
These are the main screens/views that users navigate to. They are assembled using the smaller Components.

#### General Pages
*   **`Home.jsx` / `HomePage.jsx`**: The public landing page of the application.
*   **`Login.jsx` & `Signup.jsx`**: Forms for authenticating and registering new users.
*   **`Events.jsx`**: A generic page listing all public/approved events.
*   **`analytics/Analytics.jsx`**: A page displaying charts and statistics about the system.

#### Role: Student Pages (`src/pages/student/`)
*   **`StudentDashboard.jsx`**: The home screen for students, showing quick stats and upcoming events.
*   **`StudentEvents.jsx`**: A page where students can browse and search for events to join.
*   **`StudentRegistrations.jsx`**: A page listing all the events the student has already signed up for.

#### Role: Organizer Pages (`src/pages/organizer/`)
*   **`OrganizerDashboard.jsx`**: Home screen for event organizers.
*   **`CreateEvent.jsx` / `OrganizerCreateEvent.jsx`**: A complex form where organizers propose new events, setting dates, venues, and descriptions.
*   **`Organizerparticipants.jsx`**: A page to view and manage the list of students who have registered for their events.
*   **`SubmitBudget.jsx`**: A form to propose a financial budget for an upcoming event.
*   **`PostEventReport.jsx`**: A form to submit a summary/report after an event has successfully concluded.

#### Role: Faculty Pages (`src/pages/faculty/`)
*   **`FacultyDashboard.jsx`**: Home screen for faculty members.
*   **`FacultyApprovals.jsx`**: A crucial page where faculty can see pending event proposals and choose to approve or reject them.
*   **`FacultyReports.jsx`**: A page to view post-event reports submitted by organizers.

#### Role: Head of Department (HOD) Pages (`src/pages/hod/`)
*   **`HodDashboard.jsx`**: Home screen for HODs.
*   **`HodApprovals.jsx`**: Similar to Faculty Approvals, but represents a higher level in the approval workflow.

#### Role: Student Welfare (SDW) Pages (`src/pages/sdw/`)
*   **`SDWDashboard.jsx`**: Home screen for the Dean/Student Welfare office.
*   **`SDWApprovals.jsx`**: The final stage of approvals for high-level or campus-wide events.
